html: 12.18.19  4:21 pm   12.17.19  10:40 pm the reason you don't hear about people doing this is because it's not very intuitive or obvious that this is what you should do. but it works, at least for me. even for entirely unrelated fields such as app development. building a bunch of tiny apps that do simple things is a much better way of learning than spending a ton of time on one huge project that i never end up finishing
